            <div type="translation">
                    <p>In favour of Queen Kleopatra and King Ptolemy, [or: King Ptolemy also called Alexander and Queen Kleopatra (or: Berenike his sister) the gods Philometores Soteres,  the soldiers stationed in Schedia, whose commander is the chiliarch Sosipatros, the Kleopatreion.</p>
            </div> 
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Dedication of a temple to Kleopatra III, by the garrison of Schedia, under the command of the chiliarch Sosipatros (Trismegistos P13824). The royal names and cult titles have normally been restored as referring to Ptolemy IX Soter II and Kleopatra III (116-107) but might alternatively refer to Ptolemy X Alexander I and Berenike III (101-88), see Scheuble 2009.</p>
            </div>
